channel.description:
so hey guys i'm currently making a rsps and i can the server 24-7 i have a brand new ASUS computer built with a lot of ram so i can run a 24-7 server with out lag!
Ive got JDK, i have portfowarded , ive got no-ip , ive got the source and when i check runelocus status checker when i run it , it says "ONLINE" but the thing is i tried to login with my other computer with the client and it wont work so thats where im stuck, im not sure if i compiled wrong or just made the client wrong somehow or if i didnt edit the server right. but yeah if someone can help me through team viewer i will give them owner and ill run the server 24-7
message me or text me at 928-581-8750 or just message me on here

item.title: Need help i got server online -free owner if help graunted 24-7 server
item.dc:creator: @The_Web_Guy The Web Guy
item.description:
@The_Web_Guy wrote:

Make sure you change the IP on the client, it can be in different places depending on the client revision.
For 317s it’s usually in - client.java
For 508+ check one of these - client.java, loader.java, GUI.java/EGUI.java, settings.cfg

The, ‘settings.cfg’ is usually for 677 revision.

If you still cannot find it, let me know and i’ll help through teamviewer.

item.title: Need help i got server online -free owner if help graunted 24-7 server
item.dc:creator: @Illadelph Illadelph
item.description:
@Illadelph wrote:

You cant compile it wrong lol. unless it gives you errors which is a code wrong.

But yeah client.java theres usually 1-2 ips you have to change to in yours… first one you search is 127.0.0.1 change it to your no-ip.org and then compile and let me know
Note this is client/sided

Also sometimes when you run your server check the cmd if it says running on a certain ip sometimes you have to change that and its server sided.

Another possibility is if you dont have a static-ip . Which you can check cmd-ipconfig
which is set up with portforward.( this usually gets people)
some people internet change static ip’s every now and then. or sometimes when internet is turned off and on. but thats not always the case. just another possibility
